Techs
  Most, if not all, will have NO RESOURCE COST, but may have some lengthy research durations
  
  HU
    Flare: Available at Barracks, now also allows Riflemen to use at with limited range
    Demolition Squad: Upgrade that allows Mortar Team and Dynamiters to Self-destruct, dealing heavy damage. After a short interval the sacrificed unit will be revived at its owner base
    Steam Engine morph: Allows Steam Engines to upgrade into its beta Wrecking Ball version, permanently making it a melee unit, but able to carry units inside. Riflemen can shoot from within and peasants can repair.
  Orc
    A nameless ability rather than an upgrade: Spirit Lodges can toggle how much health will be sacrificed upon training Warlocks, granting them additional mana while the higher hit point sacrifice is enabled
    Upgrade that allows Ogres to be trained at Altar!
    Tauren renamed to Tauren Bulls, and Pulverize comes researched already
  UD
    Dirt Eater: Cannibalize comes researched already, and researching Dirt Eater makes dying ghouls to summon a Dirt Eater, a sick/poisonous ghoul with lifespan increased according to how much the dying ghoul cannibalized
    Ability that allows Ghouls and other crap to "fuse" into an Abomination
    Corpse Explosion: Abomination Self-destruct, empowered by how much it cannibalized while alive
    Psychic Scream: Upgrade that causes Banshees to scream upon death, scaring enemies and making them run away from the point where they die
    Greater Summon Building: Undecided whether I'm giving Necromancers this shit or not. The idea is give the Necromancers their early development purpose, being the
                             actual builder of the faction, also allowing me to make use of cool structures I can't fit anywhere else such as Gargoyle Spire
    Necromancer ghost as an alternative unit for Greater Summon Building
    Spire: Gargoyles and Carrion Birds
    Tree of Woe: ??? something to do with Cold Wraiths?
    Heunting (a building I guess): ???
  NE
    Mark of the Wild: Same as IPRS, Huntress Hall upgrade that unlocks a new beast form for druids. Both drain mana while morph
    Moonkin Form: Druid of the Talon new morph with strong magic attacks that gain different buffs at day and night
    Cat Form: Druid of the Claw new morph with permanent invisibility, can pounce at targets and deal damage based on their maximum hit points
  
